Package eu.iv4xr.framework.mainConcepts

Class ObservationEvent

java.lang.Object
eu.iv4xr.framework.mainConcepts.ObservationEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Parsable
Direct Known Subclasses:
ObservationEvent.CoveragePointEvent, ObservationEvent.TimeStampedObservationEvent
public class ObservationEvent extends Object implements Serializable, Parsable
Observation-events represent observations that a test-agent (TestAgent) collects. There are several types of observations, such as verdict and coverage-event, represented by different subclasses of this class.

    This class is used to represent observation-events that need to be time-stamped.
    static class 
    ObservationEvent.VerdictEvent
    When a test-agent interacts with a system-under-test, it will want to report things that meet its expectations, as well as things that violate its expectations (and may thus imply bugs).
